# Astronomical Image Refiner  
**PSF Correction & Neural Enhancement**

> *‚ÄúHST-to-JWST Image Processor: 13-year PSF characterization meets next-gen mosaicking for precision multi-mission astronomy‚Äù*

---

## üöÄ What Is This?

Astronomical Image Refiner is a software framework designed to improve the quality of telescope images by combining **point spread function (PSF)** correction with **neural network‚Äìbased image enhancement**. The goal is to recover fine spatial details in astronomical data‚Äîespecially when combining images from different missions like Hubble (HST) and the James Webb Space Telescope (JWST).

This tool enables:  
- **PSF correction:** Use physically or empirically derived PSFs to deconvolve blurred images.  
- **Neural enhancement:** Deep learning models enhance structures (stars, galaxies, nebulae) while suppressing noise and artifacts.  
- **Multi-mission processing:** Integrate data from different space telescopes for unified, high-resolution mosaics.  
- **Precision science:** Produce scientifically meaningful images suitable for photometry, morphological studies, and more.

---

## üìö Why It Matters

- **PSF degradation** (due to optics + atmosphere) limits image sharpness. Deconvolution helps, but classical methods can amplify noise.  
- Neural networks can learn to ‚Äúundo‚Äù blur while preserving real astrophysical structure, based on training on realistic simulations or calibration data. Similar approaches have been published in the literature. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}  
- By combining **13 years of calibration** (e.g. from HST) with modern deep learning, this project makes high-fidelity image reconstruction more robust and accessible.

---

## üîß Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **PSF Estimation** | Characterize and model PSFs over time or spatially across the field. |
| **Deconvolution** | Use PSF models to reverse blurring (non-blind deconvolution). |
| **Neural Enhancement** | Use neural nets (e.g., U-Net, CNNs) to sharpen and clean images. |
| **Mosaicking** | Generate mosaics from multi-mission data with consistent resolution. |
| **CLI + Notebook Support** | Run from the command line, or explore via Jupyter notebooks. |
| **Extensible** | Easily add new PSF models, network architectures, or datasets. |

---

## üß™ Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/tlcagford/Astronomical-Image-Refiner-PSF-Correction-and-Neural-Enhancement.git
cd Astronomical-Image-Refiner-PSF-Correction-and-Neural-Enhancement

# Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# (Optional) install as a package
pip install .
